Project 4: INTVL Prototype (Location-Based Game)
Description: A location-based fitness game where users capture real-world territory (hexes) by physically walking or running in those locations.
Tech Stack: React (Vite), React-Leaflet, Supabase (PostGIS), H3-js (Hexagonal Hierarchical Spatial Index).
Key Features: Interactive map with real-time user tracking, "Red vs. Blue" team mechanics, territory capture logic using geospatial data, and a live leaderboard system.
Project 5: AI Viral Content Generator (CLI Tool)
Description: A Python command-line tool designed to automate content research by fetching real-time viral news and generating deep-dive brainstorming ideas.
Tech Stack: Python, RSS Feeds/News APIs, CLI (Command Line Interface).
Key Features: Menu-driven interface with auto-selection, real-time trend aggregation from web sources, and a fail-safe "AI Brainstorm" mode that generates unique topics when internet connectivity is limited.
Project 6: HomeWorld Project
Description: An interactive web platform that simulates a personalized digital homeworld where users can explore, customize, and interact with virtual elements.
Tech Stack: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Three.js.
Key Features: Immersive UI, real time object manipulation, user driven customization, interactive animations.
